## Key Finding

**{{ n_desert_lsoas|int|format_thousands }}** LSOAs have no bus stops within their boundaries, affecting approximately **{{ pop_affected|int|format_thousands }}** people. {% if largest_region %}The largest concentration of transport deserts is in **{{ largest_region }}** ({{ largest_region_count|int }} LSOAs), reflecting the structural challenge of serving dispersed rural settlements.{% endif %}

These are not areas with infrequent service — they are areas with **zero** bus infrastructure. Residents face a complete absence of public transport, making car ownership a functional necessity regardless of individual income or mobility status.

